problem_prompt: Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in biology would. Evaluate $\sqrt[3]{12}\times \sqrt[3]{20}\times \sqrt[3]{15}\times \sqrt[3]{60}$.
gpt_response:
To evaluate the given expression, we first simplify each cubed root:

$\sqrt[3]{12} = 12^{1/3} = 2$
$\sqrt[3]{20} = 20^{1/3} = 2.714$
$\sqrt[3]{15} = 15^{1/3} = 2.466$
$\sqrt[3]{60} = 60^{1/3} = 3.915$

Then we multiply these simplified values together:

$2 \times 2.714 \times 2.466 \times 3.915 = 66.537$

Therefore, $\sqrt[3]{12}\times \sqrt[3]{20}\times \sqrt[3]{15}\times \sqrt[3]{60} = 66.537$.
